data_scaled = data_scaled.applymap(lambda x: np.nan if x < 0 else x)

# Handle NaN values by imputing with the median of the respective column
for column in data_scaled.columns:
    median_value = data_scaled[column].median()
    data_scaled[column] = data_scaled[column].apply(lambda x: median_value if pd.isna(x) else x)

Q4 A Apply K-Means clustering for 2 to 10 clusters¶

In [252]:
clusters = range(2,11)
ss = []
for k in clusters:
    model = KMeans (n_clusters=k,n_init=10, max_iter=300, random_state=1)
    model.fit(data_scaled)
    ss.append(model.inertia_)

Q4 I Share your insights on the clusters which are built. Here try to explain what each cluster is saying.¶

Q4 J Considering the cluster profiles, give any 2-business recommendation which will help the business.¶

Based on the cluster profile, we can derive the following insights for each cluster:

Cluster 0:¶

  • Listing Price: 9370
  • Sale Price: 6327
  • Discount: 31.93%
  • Rating: 3.31
  • Reviews: 49.52
  • Brand: Predominantly Adidas ORIGINALS

Insights: Cluster 0 consists mainly of products from the Adidas ORIGINALS brand with a moderate listing price and discount. This cluster has a good number of reviews and ratings indicating moderately popular products.

Cluster 1:¶

  • Listing Price: 4951
  • Sale Price: 3116
  • Discount: 36.30%
  • Rating: 3.41
  • Reviews: 48.21
  • Brand: Predominantly Adidas CORE / NEO

Insights: Cluster 1 includes products mostly from the Adidas CORE / NEO brand with relatively lower listing prices and higher discounts. This cluster also has a good number of reviews and ratings, suggesting these products are quite popular among cost-sensitive customers.

Cluster 2:¶

  • Listing Price: 18413
  • Sale Price: 17042
  • Discount: 5.03%
  • Rating: 3.18
  • Reviews: 27.33
  • Brand: Mixed with Nike and some Adidas SPORT PERFORMANCE

Insights: Cluster 2 is composed of high-end products with high listing and sale prices. These products come from mixed brands, including Nike and Adidas SPORT PERFORMANCE. The discount rate is very low, and the number of reviews is comparatively lower, indicating these are premium products with a niche customer base.

Cluster 3:¶

  • Listing Price: 10044
  • Sale Price: 8734
  • Discount: 0%
  • Rating: 2.77
  • Reviews: 6.74
  • Brand: Predominantly Nike

Insights: Cluster 3 contains products primarily from the Nike brand with moderate listing prices but zero discounts. These products have low ratings and very few reviews, indicating they are less popular among customers.

Cluster 4:¶

  • Listing Price: 8126
  • Sale Price: 5267
  • Discount: 33.95%
  • Rating: 3.33
  • Reviews: 48.93
  • Brand: Predominantly Adidas SPORT PERFORMANCE

Insights: Cluster 4 is characterized by products from the Adidas SPORT PERFORMANCE brand with moderate listing prices and considerable discounts. This cluster has a healthy number of reviews and ratings, signifying these products are popular among customers looking for sports performance gear at discounted prices.

Business Recommendations¶

Based on the cluster profiles, here are two business recommendations:

1. Tailored Marketing Strategies:¶

  • Premium Segment (Cluster 2): Focus marketing efforts on highlighting the exclusivity and premium quality of high-end products from Nike and Adidas SPORT PERFORMANCE. Use targeted advertising to reach a niche, high-income customer base.
  • Discount-Oriented Segment (Clusters 1 and 4): Promote these clusters to cost-sensitive customers who are looking for quality products at a discount. Emphasize the value-for-money aspect in marketing campaigns for products from Adidas CORE / NEO and Adidas SPORT PERFORMANCE.

2. Product Improvement and Inventory Management:¶

  • Underperforming Products (Cluster 3): Investigate why Nike products in this cluster have low ratings and few reviews. Consider product improvements or re-evaluate pricing strategies to boost their attractiveness. These products may require better visibility or enhancements to meet customer expectations.
  • Popular Products (Clusters 0 and 1): Ensure adequate inventory for products in these clusters to meet demand, as they have moderate prices, good discounts, and high customer engagement. Consider expanding the product range or introducing similar products to capitalize on their popularity.

Implementing these recommendations can help the business optimize its product offerings, improve customer satisfaction, and increase overall sales.
